{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01G7uLLtAzp2pk8gKeZsg1ct","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Oracle passes. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** The Elasticsearch pods were running as orphaned (no StatefulSet controller), with only the `elasticsearch` container — no monitoring sidecars. The monitoring cluster (`monitoring-es`) hadn't been deployed yet.\n\n**Fix applied:**\n\n1. **Deployed the monitoring cluster** — applied `monitoring-es` (ES 7.17.9 single-node) and `monitoring-curl-test` into the `monitoring` namespace, creating the `monitoring-es-http` service that sidecars ship to.\n\n2. **Created metricbeat/filebeat ConfigMaps** — adapted for the current environment (ES 8.11.1, no TLS, no auth): `http://localhost:9200` as the ES source, `http://monitoring-es-http.monitoring.svc:9200` as the output.\n\n3. **Created `es-cluster` StatefulSet with sidecars** — the StatefulSet adopted the three orphaned pods and performed a rolling update (one pod at a time, keeping 2/3 nodes healthy throughout), adding `metricbeat:7.17.9` and `filebeat:7.17.9` containers and a shared `es-logs` emptyDir volume.\n\nResult: all three ES pods now run `elasticsearch + metricbeat + filebeat`, metricbeat is shipping `.monitoring-es-7-mb-*` indices to the monitoring cluster with 90+ documents, and the ES cluster remained healthy throughout."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":415,"cache_read_input_tokens":70886,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":415},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c2035853-a6a0-47d8-83e1-771664d2cff4","uuid":"3ff8d584-047b-44fa-a8c6-fb4e69718c28","request_id":"req_011Cc5T7H5ZGHJCfE6ReA6iY"}
